---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Your Name">
  <header class="container page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Curious about structure, uncertainty, and computation.</h1>
    <p>
      I am a mathematics undergraduate building a foundation in analysis,
      probability, statistics, optimization, and computation. This site collects
      my project notes, experiments, and learning record.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="container section two-column">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Academic Direction</h2>
      <p>
        My interests sit between applied mathematics and computing: modeling
        real systems, making uncertainty visible, and turning mathematical ideas
        into reproducible experiments.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am especially interested in mathematical modeling competitions,
        computational imaging, inverse problems, statistical data analysis, and
        small tools that help explain technical ideas clearly.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>What I Am Building</h2>
      <p>
        This website is intentionally simple: Markdown project pages, static
        deployment, and a structure that can later support bilingual content.
      </p>
      <p>
        Future sections may include reading notes, course reflections, code
        notebooks, and longer technical essays.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
